Class al_Example<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.software.reuze.al_Example<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    al_ExampleFOL

    public class al_Example<E>
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    Represents a learning example; according to page 699, in a Boolean decision tree it is the pair (x, y), where "x is a vector of values for the input attributes and y is a single boolean output value". This definition has been abstracted to produce this generic class.
    Author:
    Ravi Mohan, Andrew Brown
